    "body": "Hi @alcuadrado . Thanks for the reply.\r\n\r\nThe constructor arguments will be abi encoded and send along with the contract verification request:\r\nhttps://github.com/nomiclabs/buidler/blob/2a344636aea340ef927fd1409065829edde34bb1/packages/buidler-etherscan/src/index.ts#L76-L79\r\n\r\nWhile during contract deployment(the `factory.deploy(\"0xabcdef\")` code snippet in my previous comment), it was correctly encoded as `abcdef`.\r\nHowever, it was encoded as `3078616263646566` when I append `0xabcdef` to `npx buidler verify-contract  --contract-name MyContract --address DEPLOYED_CONTRACT_ADDRESS `.\r\nWhich means, instead of treating it as hex string like `factory.deploy` did,  `AbiEncoder.encodeConstructor` treat `0xabcdef` as string of ascii characters(`3078616263646566` is the ascii representation of `0xabcdef`).\r\n\r\nAnd that's why etherscan contract verification failed, as it was expecting constructor arguments to be `abcdef` but instead got `3078616263646566`.\r\n\r\nPlease let me know if it's still unclear. Thanks!",
